-- KfW Expects Market to Stay `Volatile' Through 2010, Confirms Funding Level
-- Mike Gavin
-- 2010-07-07T10:15:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/kfw-expects-market-to-stay-volatile-through-2010-confirms-funding-level.html

          
          
             KfW Group expects “market conditions
will remain volatile over the next six months, and that the
public finance situation in the eurozone will continue to
unsettle many market participants,” it said in an e-mailed
statement today.  
 The bank confirmed its anticipated funding volume of 75
billion euros for 2010.  
          
          


  


        